    "claim": "The core accounting treats `IShareToken.balanceOf(user)` as the sole source of truth for both collateral ownership and debt ownership, while `IShareToken` is an ERC20-style token interface. If the deployed share tokens permit transfers, users can move collateral shares or debt shares to a different address without any solvency check, bypassing the protocol's same-account collateral/debt invariant.",
    "impact": "A borrower can externalize debt or strip collateral out of the indebted account, then withdraw assets while leaving the protocol with uncollateralized debt that cannot be recovered from the original borrower. This is a direct insolvency vector.",
    "paths": [
      "User deposits collateral in account A, borrows another asset, transfers the collateral share tokens to account B, and account B withdraws the collateral while account A keeps the debt.",
      "User borrows in account A, transfers the debt share tokens to a throwaway account B, and account A now appears debt-free to `isSolvent`/`depositPossible`, allowing collateral withdrawal and leaving account B with naked debt."
    ]
  },
