      "0xcb3b879ab11f825885d5add8bf3672596d35197c/contracts/BaseSilo.sol:200"
    ],
    "claim": "`depositFor` is publicly callable even though it is documented as a router helper, and `borrowPossible` rejects any borrower who holds either collateral-share token for that asset. An attacker can therefore mint a tiny position for an arbitrary victim and force future borrows of that asset to revert.",
    "impact": "This is a permissionless griefing vector against borrowing and router UX. An attacker can dust many users across many supported assets, forcing each victim to discover and unwind the unwanted positions at their own gas cost before they can borrow.",
    "paths": [
      "Attacker calls `depositFor(asset, victim, 1, false)` or `depositFor(asset, victim, 1, true)`.",
      "Victim later calls `borrow(asset, amount)` and hits `BorrowNotPossible` because they now hold a nonzero collateral-share balance for that asset."
    ]
  },
